_source.body: Who knows?  Aside from the issues posed by New York’s mayor not being in that city (who runs the place in his absence?), we could, depending on the circumstances, find Mayor Eric Adams taking a significantly more realistic stance on illegal immigration than the Biden White House.  I am admittedly not holding my breath about this, but I can at least imagine Mayor Adams and other big city mayors making requests for more stronger measures to control the southern border.

_source.body:
NYC MAYOR ERIC ADAMS TO VISIT THE BORDER, BUT WILL IT BE A JOKE LIKE JOE BIDEN'S? We will find out later today if this trip by Adams is nothing but a joke or if he is serious.  I'm betting his presser will be toned down to suck up to dear ole Joe even though he sees the atrocities. I'm tired of progressives ignoring the deaths and human trafficking of kids—all IMO.

"Adams will visit a local migrant shelter, a facility that provides services to them and a Customs and Border Protection processing facility. He’ll also visit the southern border.

Adams will then hold a press conference later in the day."
